# Jackie Jin — AI Interactive Resume

An AI-powered personal portfolio site. Displays resume content with an always-visible AI chat
sidebar where visitors can ask questions about experience, skills, and projects in English or Chinese.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Recharts + Framer Motion
- **Backend**: Python FastAPI + LangChain + ChromaDB (RAG) + Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-6)
- **Deployment**: AWS — S3 + CloudFront (frontend), ECS Fargate + ALB (backend), EFS (ChromaDB)

---

## Project Structure

### Backend (`backend/`)

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `main.py` | FastAPI app entry point with CORS |
| `routes/chat.py` | `POST /api/chat` — SSE streaming chat endpoint |
| `routes/resume.py` | `GET /api/resume` and `GET /api/resume/projects` |
| `routes/github.py` | `GET /api/github/stats` — GitHub API proxy with 1hr cache |
| `rag/chain.py` | RAG chain: ChromaDB retrieval → Claude streaming response |
| `rag/embedder.py` | Embeds resume YAML docs into ChromaDB (run once on setup) |
| `data/resume.yaml` | **Source of truth** — edit this with your real info |
| `data/projects.yaml` | Project details for showcase + RAG |

### Frontend (`frontend/`)

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `src/app/page.tsx` | Main page — 70/30 side-by-side resume + chat layout |
| `src/app/projects/page.tsx` | Project showcase grid (featured + other) |
| `src/app/stats/page.tsx` | GitHub stats + language pie chart |
| `src/components/chat/ChatPanel.tsx` | AI chat with SSE streaming + Recruiter Mode |
| `src/components/chat/SuggestedQuestions.tsx` | Suggested question chips |
| `src/components/resume/AboutSection.tsx` | Name, title, bio, open-to-work badge |
| `src/components/resume/ExperienceSection.tsx` | Work history timeline |
| `src/components/resume/SkillsSection.tsx` | Language bars + skill tag clouds |
| `src/components/resume/EducationSection.tsx` | Education + certifications |
| `src/components/visualizations/SkillsRadar.tsx` | Recharts radar chart for skill proficiency |
| `src/components/visualizations/CareerTimeline.tsx` | Animated career + education timeline |
| `src/components/visualizations/TechWordCloud.tsx` | Weighted tech stack word cloud |
| `src/components/projects/ProjectCard.tsx` | Project card with tech badges + impact |
| `src/components/Navbar.tsx` | Nav with dark/light mode toggle + PDF download |

---

## Features

- Side-by-side layout: resume on the left, AI chat always visible on the right
- AI chat powered by Claude API with RAG over resume data
- Suggested questions + Recruiter Mode (paste a JD to analyze fit)
- Bilingual: AI auto-detects English / Chinese and responds accordingly
- Interactive visualizations: Skills Radar, Career Timeline, Tech Word Cloud
- Project showcase with GitHub stats (stars/forks via GitHub API)
- GitHub language breakdown pie chart
- Dark / light mode
- Open to Work status badge

---

## Setup

### 1. Configure backend

```bash
cp backend/.env.example backend/.env
# Edit backend/.env — add your ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, GITHUB_TOKEN, GITHUB_USERNAME
```

### 2. Install backend dependencies

```bash
cd backend
python -m venv .venv
.venv/Scripts/pip install -r requirements.txt   # Windows
# or: .venv/bin/pip install -r requirements.txt  # Mac/Linux
```

### 3. Embed resume into ChromaDB (run once, re-run after data changes)

```bash
cd backend
.venv/Scripts/python rag/embedder.py
```

### 4. Start the backend

```bash
cd backend
.venv/Scripts/uvicorn main:app --reload
# API available at http://localhost:8000
```

### 5. Configure and start the frontend

```bash
cd frontend
cp .env.local.example .env.local
npm install
npm run dev
# App available at http://localhost:3000
```

---

## Customization

Edit `backend/data/resume.yaml` with your real name, experience, skills, and education.
Edit `backend/data/projects.yaml` with your real projects.
After editing, re-run `rag/embedder.py` to update the AI's knowledge base.

---

## AWS Deployment

**Live URL**: https://d33qsa6f99h2bi.cloudfront.net

**Architecture**: CloudFront → S3 (frontend static export) + ALB → ECS Fargate (FastAPI backend) + EFS (ChromaDB)

### Redeploy frontend
```bash
cd frontend
npm run build
aws s3 sync out/ s3://myresume-frontend-041875151540/ --delete --region ap-southeast-2
aws cloudfront create-invalidation --distribution-id E2VLNB8O1DB4Y7 --paths "/*" --region us-east-1
```

### Redeploy backend
```bash
docker build -t myresume-backend ./backend
docker tag myresume-backend:latest 041875151540.dkr.ecr.ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/myresume-backend:latest
docker push 041875151540.dkr.ecr.ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/myresume-backend:latest
aws ecs update-service --cluster myresume-cluster --service myresume-backend-service --force-new-deployment --region ap-southeast-2
```

### Re-embed after data changes
After editing `resume.yaml` or `projects.yaml`, push new backend image then run the embedder as a one-off ECS task:
```bash
aws ecs run-task \
  --cluster myresume-cluster \
  --task-definition myresume-backend \
  --launch-type FARGATE \
  --network-configuration "awsvpcConfiguration={subnets=[subnet-03ff39fd91d5192dd],securityGroups=[sg-0cfa3c2e86d87e0a0],assignPublicIp=ENABLED}" \
  --overrides '{"containerOverrides":[{"name":"backend","command":["python","rag/embedder.py"]}]}' \
  --region ap-southeast-2
```
